		<div class="post-1808 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-art category-quilting" id="post-1808">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/03/02/trapplique/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Trapplique!">Trapplique!</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Trapplique-closeup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1809" title="Trapplique closeup" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Trapplique-closeup-640x480.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="480" /></a></p>
<p>Oh how I love this combination of applique and trapunto. I wasn&#8217;t sure what to call it: <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=double+applique&amp;ie=utf-8&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;aq=t&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&amp;client=firefox-a#hl=en&amp;sugexp=ldymls&amp;pq=double%20applique&amp;xhr=t&amp;q=%22double+trapunto%22&amp;cp=17&amp;qe=ImRvdWJsZSB0cmFwdW50byI&amp;qesig=_20zlRz2PSem4q6S74c-cA&amp;pkc=AFgZ2tmOgHs9dn63orZfwafmo6jcIOWxWazmqwu8k4049YYOUhYhMw_qVO8UgTddtVUkbuoFUimRqxdVLEmaCRCb6gVRu8TyHQ&amp;pf=p&amp;sclient=psy&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;hs=mIz&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US%3Aofficial&amp;aq=f&amp;aqi=&amp;aql=&amp;oq=%22double+trapunto%22&amp;pbx=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.&amp;fp=eb3207f822e70c41">double trapunto</a>? <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=double+applique&amp;ie=utf-8&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;aq=t&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&amp;client=firefox-a#hl=en&amp;sugexp=ldymls&amp;pq=double%20trapunto&amp;xhr=t&amp;q=trapplique&amp;cp=3&amp;qe=dHJh&amp;qesig=4v_HTfdAPi8AENcWzLt0qg&amp;pkc=AFgZ2tn7yD29YRY3hNu25uYhA2moPJ1v11Dg1hmIcsbOj8ozm2gjn5Kr7aDnmpkQtn1FXf0L8a7D9iQFc8Cou4sQAn9JVWowhA&amp;pf=p&amp;sclient=psy&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;hs=ryJ&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US%3Aofficial&amp;aq=0p&amp;aqi=&amp;aql=&amp;oq=tra&amp;pbx=1&amp;bav=on.2,or.&amp;fp=eb3207f822e70c41">Trapplique</a>? It&#8217;s not a technique I&#8217;d seen before, but I&#8217;m sure others have done it because it&#8217;s obvious. Anyway, this technique is for me.</p>
<div id="attachment_1810" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/finished.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1810" title="finished" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/finished-640x480.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="480" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Hippie Hand</p></div>
<p>This is actually a test for a larger piece I&#8217;m making for my wall. It&#8217;s in the Hippie craft tradition I so admired in my youth, so pardon the Orientalism &#8211; it&#8217;s an integral part of American Hippiedom. The pattern on the hand is based on <a href="http://www.google.com/images?q=mehendi&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;um=1&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;source=univ&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=vMttTf3cIZDqgQfSyeH9Aw&amp;ved=0CDMQsAQ&amp;biw=1232&amp;bih=1021">mehendi</a>, the spirally flames on <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Tibetan-tapestry-cloud.jpg">Tibetan art</a>, and the eye in the palm of the hand is plain ol&#8217; Hippie mysticism.  <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/03/02/trapplique/#more-1808" class="more-link">Continue reading Trapplique!</a></p>
<div class="plus-one-wrap"><g:plusone href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/03/02/trapplique/"></g:plusone></div><p class="wp-flattr-button"><a class="FlattrButton" style="display:none;" href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/03/02/trapplique/" title=" Trapplique!" rev="flattr;uid:ninapaley;language:en_GB;category:text;tags:blog;button:compact;">Oh how I love this combination of applique and trapunto. I wasn&#8217;t sure what to call it: double trapunto? Trapplique? It&#8217;s not a technique I&#8217;d seen before, but I&#8217;m sure...</a></p><div class="addtoany_share_save_container"><div class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_target addtoany_list" id="wpa2a_14"><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save" href="http://www.addtoany.com/share_save" style="background:url(http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/plugins/add-to-any/favicon.png) no-repeat scroll 4px 0px !important;padding:0 0 0 25px;display:inline-block;height:16px;vertical-align:middle">Share/Bookmark</a></div></div></div>

<div class="post-footer">March 2nd, 2011 |  Category: <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/art/" title="View all posts in art" rel="category tag">art</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/quilting/" title="View all posts in quilting" rel="category tag">quilting</a> | <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/03/02/trapplique/#comments" class="comments-link"  title="Comment on Trapplique!">20 comments</a> </div>
</div><!-- / Post -->						
	
	

		
			



